wwpLeosPortMIB.name: wwpLeosPortMIB

revisions.description: Added wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertSpeed and wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertDuplex to WwpLeosEtherPortEntry MIB object
Added admitOnlyUntagged to wwpLeosEtherPortAcceptableFrameTypes MIB object
Added wwpLeosEtherFixedRColor and wwpLeosEtherPortFrameCosMapId mib objects
Added changed length of wwpLeosPortDescr from 32 to 128.
Added wwpLeosEtherPortEgressPortQueueMapId to wwpLeosEtherPortEntryTable. Added 10 gig option to wwpLeosEtherInterfaceType, wwpLeosEtherAdminSpeed and wwpLeosEtherOperSpeed

Added new mib object wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupOperStatus. Added new mib object wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumSrcPorts. Added new mib object wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumDstPorts. Added new mib object wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemOperState.
This MIB module is for the Extension of the dot1dBasePortTable for WWP Products
Added new tables to support port state mirroring feature.

wwpLeosPortMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosPortMIB.description: This MIB defines the managed objects for Ethernet ports.

PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

PortEgressFrameCosPolicy.name: PortEgressFrameCosPolicy
PortEgressFrameCosPolicy.description: Egress cos policy to use on this port ignore means leave egress map disabled

PortIngressFixedColor.name: PortIngressFixedColor
PortIngressFixedColor.description: Egress cos policy to use on this port ignore means leave egress map disabled

wwpLeosEtherPortEntry.name: wwpLeosEtherPortEntry
wwpLeosEtherPortEntry.description: Port Entry in the Ethernet Port Table.

wwpLeosEtherPortId.name: wwpLeosEtherPortId
wwpLeosEtherPortId.description: Port ID for the instance. Port ID's start at 1, and may not be consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpLeosEtherPortName.name: wwpLeosEtherPortName
wwpLeosEtherPortName.description: A textual string containing information about the port. This string should indicate about the physical location of the port as well.

wwpLeosEtherPortDesc.name: wwpLeosEtherPortDesc
wwpLeosEtherPortDesc.description: A textual string containing port description.

wwpLeosEtherPortType.name: wwpLeosEtherPortType
wwpLeosEtherPortType.description: The port type for the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortPhysAddr.name: wwpLeosEtherPortPhysAddr
wwpLeosEtherPortPhysAddr.description: The ethernet MAC address for the port. This information can also be achieved via dot1dTpFdbTable

wwpLeosEtherPortAutoNeg.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAutoNeg
wwpLeosEtherPortAutoNeg.description: The object sets the port to AUTO NEG MOde and vice versa. Specific platforms may have requirements of configuring speed before moving the port to out of AUTO-NEG mode.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdminStatus.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdminStatus
wwpLeosEtherPortAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortOperStatus.name: wwpLeosEtherPortOperStatus
wwpLeosEtherPortOperStatus.description: The current operational state of Port.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdminSpeed.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdminSpeed
wwpLeosEtherPortAdminSpeed.description: Desired speed of the port. Set the port speed to be either 10MB, 100MB, or gig. Set the port speed to auto to enable automatic port speed detection. The default value for this object depends upon the platform.

wwpLeosEtherPortOperSpeed.name: wwpLeosEtherPortOperSpeed
wwpLeosEtherPortOperSpeed.description: The current operational speed of the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdminDuplex.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdminDuplex
wwpLeosEtherPortAdminDuplex.description: The desired mode for the port. It can be set to either half or full duplex operation. The default value for this object depends upon the platform.

wwpLeosEtherPortOperDuplex.name: wwpLeosEtherPortOperDuplex
wwpLeosEtherPortOperDuplex.description: The current duplex mode of the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdminFlowCtrl.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdminFlowCtrl
wwpLeosEtherPortAdminFlowCtrl.description: Configures the ports flow control operation.

wwpLeosEtherIngressPvid.name: wwpLeosEtherIngressPvid
wwpLeosEtherIngressPvid.description: The Ingress PVID, the VLAN ID associated with untagged frames ingressing the port or if tunnel is enabled on this port. The max value for this object is platform dependent. Refer to architecture document for details of platform dependency.

wwpLeosEtherUntagEgressVlanId.name: wwpLeosEtherUntagEgressVlanId
wwpLeosEtherUntagEgressVlanId.description: All the egress frames whose VLAN id matches the wwpLeosEtherUntagEgressVlanId, will egress the port as untagged. To egress the frames tagged set wwpLeosEtherUntagEgressVlanId to 0. The max value for this object is platform dependent. Refer to architecture document for details of platform dependency.

wwpLeosEtherPortAcceptableFrameTypes.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAcceptableFrameTypes
wwpLeosEtherPortAcceptableFrameTypes.description: When this is admitOnlyVlanTagged(2) the device will discard untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port. When admitOnlyUntagged(3) is set, the device will discard VLAN tagged frames received on this port. With admitOnlyUntagged(3) and admitAll(1), untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port will be accepted and assigned to the PVID for this port. This control does not affect VLAN independent BPDU frames, such as GVRP and STP. It does affect VLAN dependent BPDU frames, such as GMRP.

wwpLeosEtherPortUntaggedPriority.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUntaggedPriority
wwpLeosEtherPortUntaggedPriority.description: The 802.1p packet priority to be assigned to packets ingressing this port that do not have an 802.1Q VLAN header. This priority is also assigned to ingress frame if tunnel is enabled on this port.

wwpLeosEtherPortMaxFrameSize.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMaxFrameSize
wwpLeosEtherPortMaxFrameSize.description: Setting this object will set the max frame size allowed on a port. The max frame size can vary from 1522 bytes to 9216 bytes. Default value is 1526 bytes.

wwpLeosEtherPortVlanIngressFiltering.name: wwpLeosEtherPortVlanIngressFiltering
wwpLeosEtherPortVlanIngressFiltering.description: When this is true(1) the device will discard incoming frames for VLANs which do not include this Port in its Member set. When false(2), the port will accept all incoming frames.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdminAdvertisedFlowCtrl.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdminAdvertisedFlowCtrl
wwpLeosEtherPortAdminAdvertisedFlowCtrl.description: This object specifies the advertised flow control for given port.

wwpLeosEtherPortVplsPortType.name: wwpLeosEtherPortVplsPortType
wwpLeosEtherPortVplsPortType.description: This object specifies whether port is in subscriber type, network facing side or both.

wwpLeosEtherPortIngressCosPolicy.name: wwpLeosEtherPortIngressCosPolicy
wwpLeosEtherPortIngressCosPolicy.description: This object specifies the ingress cos policy to be applied to all frames coming in on the given port.

wwpLeosEtherPortIngressFixedDot1dPri.name: wwpLeosEtherPortIngressFixedDot1dPri
wwpLeosEtherPortIngressFixedDot1dPri.description: The 802.1p packet priority to be assigned to packets ingressing this port that do not have an 802.1Q VLAN header. This priority is also assigned to ingress untagged frame if the virtual switch cos policy is set to 'fix' for a given port.

wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsi.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsi
wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsi.description: This object specifies the virtual switch to be used for this port if data frame is untagged. If this object is set to 0 then device will unset this object. When setting this object to Mpls Vsi Index then wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsiType must also be set to mpls (Use multiple set operation)

wwpLeosEtherPortOperationalSpeed.name: wwpLeosEtherPortOperationalSpeed
wwpLeosEtherPortOperationalSpeed.description: An estimate of the port's current bandwidth in k-bits per second for given port.

wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsi.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsi
wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsi.description: This object specifies the virtual switch to be used for this port if control frame is untagged. If this object is set to 0 then device will unset this object. When setting this object to Mpls Vsi Index then wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsiType must also be set to mpls (Use multiple set operation)

wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorPort.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorPort
wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorPort.description: This object defines whether the port will allow traffic from other ports to be mirrored to this port. To allow traffic from other ports to be sent to this port, set this object to True(1). This port is known as a mirror port. If set to true, then other ports may set the values of their wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorIngress or wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEgress objects to the port index of this port. Setting this object to false(2) disables this port as a mirror port.

wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorIngress.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorIngress
wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorIngress.description: The value of this object is the port index of a mirror port. The ingress traffic of this port can be mirrored by setting the destination port's wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorPort object to true. If the value of this object is set to zero this port's ingress traffic will not be mirrored.

wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEgress.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEgress
wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEgress.description: The value of this object is the port index of a mirror port. The egress traffic of this port can be mirrored by setting the destination port's wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorPort object to true. If the value of this object is set to zero this port's egress traffic will not be mirrored.

wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsiType.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsiType
wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsiType.description: This object specifies the virtual switch instance type associated with this port. This object defaults to ethernet and specifies if wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsi belongs to ethernet virtual switch table (wwpLeosVplsVirtualSwitchEthTable in WWP-LEOS-VPLS-MIB) or mpls virtual switch table (wwpLeosVplsVirtualSwitchMplsTable in WWP-LEOS-VPLS-MIB). When setting wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVsi to MPLS Vsi Index then this object must also be set to mpls (Use mutliple set operation).

wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsiType.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsiType
wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsiType.description: This object specifies the virtual switch instance type associated with this port. This object defaults to ethernet and specifies if wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsi belongs to ethernet virtual switch table (wwpLeosVplsVirtualSwitchEthTable) or mpls virtual switch table (wwpLeosVplsVirtualSwitchMplsTable). When setting wwpLeosEtherPortUntagCtrlVsi to MPLS Vsi Index then this object must also be set to mpls (Use mutliple set operation)

wwpLeosEtherPortVsIngressFiltering.name: wwpLeosEtherPortVsIngressFiltering
wwpLeosEtherPortVsIngressFiltering.description: This item is applicable to this port when the port is added as a per-port member to a virtual switch. If true(1) the device will discard incoming tagged frames. If false(2) the device will forwared incoming tagged frames so long as those customer tagged frames do not match another virtual switch with this port included as a per-port-per-vlan member.

wwpLeosEtherPortOperAutoNeg.name: wwpLeosEtherPortOperAutoNeg
wwpLeosEtherPortOperAutoNeg.description: The object specifies the operational auto neg state.

wwpLeosEtherPortUpTime.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUpTime
wwpLeosEtherPortUpTime.description: The object specifies the port up time in hundredths of a second.

wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVid.name: wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVid
wwpLeosEtherPortUntagDataVid.description: The Ingress Untagged Data Vid, the VLAN ID stamped on untagged frames ingressing the port or if tunnel is enabled on this port. To disable tagging of untagged data on ingress write a value of 0. The max value for this object is platform dependent. Refer to architecture document for details of platform dependency.

wwpLeosEtherPortPhyLoopback.name: wwpLeosEtherPortPhyLoopback
wwpLeosEtherPortPhyLoopback.description: This object defines whether the phy has been placed in loopback mode, which causes frames egressing the port to be looped back to the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortVlanIngressFilterStrict.name: wwpLeosEtherPortVlanIngressFilterStrict
wwpLeosEtherPortVlanIngressFilterStrict.description: This item is applicable to this port when the port is added as a to a virtual switch. If true(1) the legacy ingress filter behavior will be enforced at member addition (drop bit will be set to drop untagged traffic). If false, the splat bit will not be changed. Note that external VLAN associations are also maintained when strict is false.

wwpLeosEtherPortMacSaDaSwap.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMacSaDaSwap
wwpLeosEtherPortMacSaDaSwap.description: This object defines whether the MAC SA and DA will be swapped on frames egressing the port. This only works on a 311V.

wwpLeosEtherPortMacSaDaSwapVlan.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMacSaDaSwapVlan
wwpLeosEtherPortMacSaDaSwapVlan.description: This object defines whether the MAC SA and DA will be swapped on specific VLAN frames egressing the port. This only works on a 311V.

wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosPolicy.name: wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosPolicy
wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosPolicy.description: The Resolved Cost Policy. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortMode.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMode
wwpLeosEtherPortMode.description: The mode of the port Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherFixedRcos.name: wwpLeosEtherFixedRcos
wwpLeosEtherFixedRcos.description: The fixed Resolve Cost value. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortEgressPortQueueMapId.name: wwpLeosEtherPortEgressPortQueueMapId
wwpLeosEtherPortEgressPortQueueMapId.description: The Egress-port-Queue associated with this port. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosMapId.name: wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosMapId
wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosMapId.description: RCOS map id for the port. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosRemarkL2.name: wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosRemarkL2
wwpLeosEtherPortResolvedCosRemarkL2.description: The object specifies whether to remark L2 based on L3. This applies when the resolved cos policy is either l3-dscp-cos or dot1d-tag1-cos but not when it is fixed-cos policy. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortL2TransformMode.name: wwpLeosEtherPortL2TransformMode
wwpLeosEtherPortL2TransformMode.description: L2 transform action for port. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapDetection.name: wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapDetection
wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapDetection.description: This object defines whether link flap detection will be enabled on the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapCount.name: wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapCount
wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapCount.description: This object defines how many link down events are required to trigger a link flap event.

wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapDetectTime.name: wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapDetectTime
wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapDetectTime.description: This object defines the time in seconds during which link down events are accumlated to trigger a link flap event.

wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapHoldTime.name: wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapHoldTime
wwpLeosEtherPortLinkFlapHoldTime.description: This object defines the time in seconds that a port will be operationally disabled after a link flap event, before it is re-enabled. A value of zero causes the port to remain disabled until manually enabled.

wwpLeosEtherFixedRColor.name: wwpLeosEtherFixedRColor
wwpLeosEtherFixedRColor.description: This sets the fixed color to green (default) or yellow. Setting this attribute is not supported in saos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortFrameCosMapId.name: wwpLeosEtherPortFrameCosMapId
wwpLeosEtherPortFrameCosMapId.description: Frame COS map id for the port. Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortEgressCosPolicy.name: wwpLeosEtherPortEgressCosPolicy
wwpLeosEtherPortEgressCosPolicy.description: Sets the egress frame cos policy Setting this attribute is not supported in leos version 4

wwpLeosEtherPortEgressSpeed.name: wwpLeosEtherPortEgressSpeed
wwpLeosEtherPortEgressSpeed.description: An estimate of the port's current egress bandwidth restriction in k-bits per second for given port. A value of 0 means there is no active restriction. This attribute not supported in leos version 6

wwpLeosEtherPortAdaptiveRateSpeed.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdaptiveRateSpeed
wwpLeosEtherPortAdaptiveRateSpeed.description: An estimate of the port's current adaptive-rate bandwidth restriction in k-bits per second for given port. A value of 0 means there is no active restriction. This attribute not supported in leos version 6

wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncap.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncap
wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncap.description: This object defines whether the port will encapsulate mirrored frames by adding a vlan-tag. (Or, in the case where a mirrored frame is already tagged, by adding a further vlan-tag to the frame) To allow mirrored traffic to be encapsulated, set this object to vlan-tag(1). If set to vlan-tag, then the values of wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapVid and wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapTpid will be used to populate tag added to each mirrored frame. Setting this object to none(0) indicates no tag is to be added to the mirrored frames.

wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapVid.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapVid
wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapVid.description: This object defines the VID that will be added to mirrored frames when the mirroring encapsulation mode is vlan-tag

wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapTpid.name: wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapTpid
wwpLeosEtherPortMirrorEncapTpid.description: This object defines the tpid used in the tag that is added to mirrored frames, when the mirroring encapsulation mode is vlan-tag

wwpLeosEtherPortIfgDecrease.name: wwpLeosEtherPortIfgDecrease
wwpLeosEtherPortIfgDecrease.description: This object defines the number of bytes that will be subtracted from the minimum standard IFG of 12 bytes as defined in IEEE 802.3. SAOS 6.x only supports a value of 0 or 4.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertSpeed.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertSpeed
wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertSpeed.description: This object defines the speed capabilities that will be advertised during the auto-negotiation process.

wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertDuplex.name: wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertDuplex
wwpLeosEtherPortAdvertDuplex.description: This object defines the duplex capabilities that will be advertised during the auto-negotiation process.

wwpLeosEtherPortFlushEntry.name: wwpLeosEtherPortFlushEntry
wwpLeosEtherPortFlushEntry.description: Broadcast containment port entry in the Ethernet Port Table.

wwpLeosEtherPortFlushActivate.name: wwpLeosEtherPortFlushActivate
wwpLeosEtherPortFlushActivate.description: Setting this object to 'true' will cause the Macs to be flushed for the port specified by wwpLeosEtherPortId.

wwpLeosEtherPortTrapsEntry.name: wwpLeosEtherPortTrapsEntry
wwpLeosEtherPortTrapsEntry.description: Port Traps Entry in the Ethernet Port Trap Table.

wwpLeosEtherPortTrapsState.name: wwpLeosEtherPortTrapsState
wwpLeosEtherPortTrapsState.description: Setting this object will enable or disable all traps on given port.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupTable.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupTable
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupTable.description: This table can be used to keep track of all the port state mirror groups. To create entry in this table along with indexes following mib objects must be set using multiple set operation wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupName must be valid string. wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupStatus must be set.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupEntry.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupEntry
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupEntry.description: Each entry in this table will define the port state mirror group.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupId.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupId
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupId.description: This mib object is used as index in the table and is used to identify the unique group id.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupName.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupName
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupName.description: This mib object is used to specify the name of the group.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupOperStat.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupOperStatus
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupOperStat.description: This mib object is used to specify the operational status of the group.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumSrcPo.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumSrcPorts
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumSrcPo.description: This mib object is used to specify the total number of source ports that exists in the group.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumDstPo.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumDstPorts
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupNumDstPo.description: This mib object is used to specify the total number of destination ports that exists in the group.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupStatus.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupStatus
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupType.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupType
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupType.description: This mib object is used to specify the directional mode type for the port state mirror group. A uni-directional(1) mirror group type will only mirror the port state of the source port(s) to the destination port(s). The bi-directional(2) mirror group type will mirror state of either the source port(s) to the destination port(s) or the state of the destination port(s) will be mirrored to the source port(s). Where there are more than one source or destination ports the combined state of the source or destination group will be the combined 'OR'ed status of all the ports in either the source or destination groups. In other words, if one or more source ports is 'UP' then the source group is 'UP' and the mirrored destination state may be 'UP'. The default for this object type is uni-directional.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemTable.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemTable
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemTable.description: This table is used to keep track of port group membership.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemEntry.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemEntry
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemEntry.description: Each entry in this table is used to represent the membership of port to a given group and group type.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemType.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemType
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemType.description: Setting this object will specify the type of group this port is member of for a given port state mirror group. This object can only be set while creating the entry. This object cannot be modified once entry is created.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemOperS.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemOperState
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemOperS.description: This mib object is used to specify the operational status of the port.

wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemStatu.name: wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemStatus
wwpLeosEtherPortStateMirrorGroupMemStatu.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table.

wwpLeosEtherStndLinkUpDownTrapsEnable.name: wwpLeosEtherStndLinkUpDownTrapsEnable
wwpLeosEtherStndLinkUpDownTrapsEnable.description: Setting this object to 'false(2)' will cause standard Link Up Down Traps to be suppressed.

wwpLeosEtherPortLinkUpDownTrapsEnable.name: wwpLeosEtherPortLinkUpDownTrapsEnable
wwpLeosEtherPortLinkUpDownTrapsEnable.description: Setting this object to 'true(1)' will cause wwp specific port up down trap to be generated.

wwpLeosEtherAggPortLinkUpDownTrapsEnable.name: wwpLeosEtherAggPortLinkUpDownTrapsEnable
wwpLeosEtherAggPortLinkUpDownTrapsEnable.description: Setting this object to 'true(1)' will cause wwp specific agg port up down trap to be generated for a link state change on a physical port that is a member of a agg.

wwpLeosEthLinkUp.name: wwpLeosEthLinkUp
wwpLeosEthLinkUp.description: A wwpLeosEthLinkUp trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links has entered the up state.

wwpLeosEthLinkDown.name: wwpLeosEthLinkDown
wwpLeosEthLinkDown.description: A wwpLeosEthLinkDown trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links has entered the down state.

wwpLeosEthAdminSpeedIncompatible.name: wwpLeosEthAdminSpeedIncompatible
wwpLeosEthAdminSpeedIncompatible.description: A wwpLeosEthAdminSpeedIncompatible trap is generated when the port administrative speed doesn't match the speed of the SFP transceiver installed.

wwpLeosEthLinkFlap.name: wwpLeosEthLinkFlap
wwpLeosEthLinkFlap.description: A wwpLeosEthLinkFlap trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links has been changed due to link flap detection.

wwpLeosAggLinkUpDown.name: wwpLeosAggLinkUpDown
wwpLeosAggLinkUpDown.description: A wwpLeosAggLinkUpDown trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links has changed state.
